The paper combines Markov Logic Networks (MLNs) and Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) to address knowledge graph problems. MLNs are a probabilistic graphical model that combines logic rules, which suggests cs.AI and cs.CL as likely sub-categories. GNNs are used for large-scale graph problems, which suggests cs.LG and cs.DB as likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new GNN variant, which suggests cs.SI as a possible sub-category.
